photos.description: | Facebook | Website | Blog | Photo Tours | Like my facebook page for more frequent updates on travels, photos, tips, tutorials and photographic expeditions. Please view this image on my website where it will display against a dark background at it's intended resolution. Even when seeing this mountain of ice with your own eyes it's still hard to comprehend it's scale. The only clue in this image that does it justice are the two people on the viewing deck in the bottom left hand corner. I wish I could upload a larger version of the image, but it would cause too many internet browser compatibility issues. This is a panorama of 13 images taken with a D800 and the 70-200 f/4. It totals a whopping 190 megapixels of pin sharp detail. I could never justify the cost of printing this at it's native resolution, but hopefully I can find someone who's willing to!
